{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_75","type":"agent_message","text":"Updated [index.json](/home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/7998-234abfdc/metadata/io.vertx/vertx-web-client/index.json) and [reachability-metadata.json](/home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/7998-234abfdc/metadata/io.vertx/vertx-web-client/5.0.1/reachability-metadata.json). I kept the `5.0.1` bucket, fixed the invalid `condition.typeReached` values so they point at `io.vertx.ext.web.client...`, restored the dropped Netty ref-count/JCTools field registrations, and re-added the older `DirectByteBuffer` / `sun.misc.Unsafe` / `jdk.internal.misc.Unsafe` registrations.\n\nI verified everything with the required GraalVM:\n`native-image 25.0.2 2026-01-20`\n`Oracle GraalVM 25.1.0-dev+10.1`\n\n`./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1` now passes. `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1` still fails after a clean rebuild with the same runtime error: `java.lang.NullPointerException` in `io.netty.util.internal.PlatformDependent0.safeConstructPutInt`, reached from `ReferenceCountUpdater.setInitialValue` / `AdaptivePoolingAllocator$Chunk.<init>`. So the metadata entries are repaired enough to validate, but the native runtime issue is still unresolved and likely sits in transitive Netty 4.2.2 / `vertx-core` coverage rather than only this `vertx-web-client` bucket."}}
